  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nRight now, `getGasPrice` on L2 geth returns 1gwei. However, no accounts in L2 are currently funded with ETH, so they can't pay their fees on L2. This means that no transactions will go through on L2 unless `gasPrice` is hardcoded to 0. We need to fund a set of L2 accounts with ETH from L1.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nOn startup, we can just `getAccounts` from the L1 chain to get all of the accounts with 1000 ETH on L1 and deposit 100 of that ETH to L2 geth from each of those accounts.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIf we want to solve this issue in the short term, we can have `gasPrice` in L2 be set to 0 gwei.\r\n",
