    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'd like for the initial state dump to have the same schema as the genesis file. It would really simplify things. The problem is that the state dump format has the ABIs and we depend on them while the genesis file format doesn't include ABIs. Perhaps we could extend the genesis file format to include the ABIs which would get parsed by opti-geth but otherwise ignored by normal geth. This would enable us to reduce the diff by getting rid of the opti-geth specific state application logic for the initial state\r\n\r\n> Currently we use the dev mode genesis file and that feels overloaded.\r\n\r\nI agree that this is overloaded, we do have plans to move away from using the clique `consensus.Engine`",
